libltc
------------------------------------------
Linear (or Longitudinal) Timecode (LTC) is an encoding of timecode data as a
Manchester-Biphase encoded audio signal. The audio signal is commonly recorded
on a VTR track or other storage media.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.6-1
  cygwin-devel-3.0.6-1
  libltc-devel-1.3.1-1bl1
  libltc11-1.3.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.0-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://x42.github.io/libltc/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/x42/libltc/archive/v1.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libltc-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libltc-1.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libltc-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libltc-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libltc11-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libltc-devel-1.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libltc)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libltc.README
  /usr/share/doc/libltc/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libltc/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libltc/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libltc/README.md

(libltc11)
  /usr/bin/cygltc-11.dll

(libltc-devel)
  /usr/include/ltc.h
  /usr/lib/libltc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ltc.pc
  /usr/share/man/man3/ltc.h.3.gz

